01:04.724 --> 01:07.743
Hi. Come on in.

01:08.778 --> 01:10.362
Amazing house, huh?

01:10.364 --> 01:12.247
Oh, you see one Hamptons
mansion, you've seen 'em all.

01:12.249 --> 01:14.566
Uh, we'll see about that.

01:14.568 --> 01:17.068
Ta-da.

01:17.070 --> 01:18.670
Whoa.

01:18.672 --> 01:20.122
The next big item up for auction

01:20.124 --> 01:21.873
by Sutton & Chesterfield.

01:21.875 --> 01:24.459
It's a T. Bataar,
first cousin of the T. Rex.

01:24.461 --> 01:25.794
Hey, Russel.

01:25.796 --> 01:27.512
- And this is Monique.
- Ah.

01:27.514 --> 01:30.048
Uh, Monique, the doctor
I called for you is here.

01:30.050 --> 01:32.083
Do you wanna take a break?

01:32.085 --> 01:33.802
You know my answer to that question.

01:33.804 --> 01:35.020
Oh, it wasn't a question.

01:35.022 --> 01:37.189
[Chuckles]

01:37.191 --> 01:39.191
- This is Hank.
- Hello.

01:39.193 --> 01:40.776
Hey.

01:40.778 --> 01:43.562
I'm going to help Russel
catalog your masterpiece,

01:43.564 --> 01:47.315
so you kids have fun.

01:47.317 --> 01:48.767
[Sighs]
I told them I was fine,

01:48.769 --> 01:51.119
but they didn't wanna take any chances.

01:51.121 --> 01:52.571
I'm their meal ticket at the moment.

01:52.573 --> 01:54.873
[Laughs]
I sense some genuine concern also,

01:54.875 --> 01:56.107
but they tell me I'm an optimist.

01:56.109 --> 01:58.744
[Laughs]
Have a seat.

01:58.746 --> 02:01.112
So what's going on?

02:01.114 --> 02:03.048
Well...
[Sighs]

02:03.050 --> 02:05.467
I've got these bug bites and a rash

02:05.469 --> 02:07.552
all over my arms and legs.

02:07.554 --> 02:08.804
Hmm. Do they itch?

02:08.806 --> 02:11.423
- Yeah, a little bit.
- Okay.

02:11.425 --> 02:12.641
Where have you been recently?

02:12.643 --> 02:14.142
I spent most of the summer in Florida

02:14.144 --> 02:16.795
doing the initial assembly of the bones.

02:16.797 --> 02:19.765
But last week, I did
a raptor dig in North Dakota.

02:19.767 --> 02:22.317
Lots of time outdoors, I assume.

02:22.319 --> 02:23.568
I slept in a sleeping bag.

02:23.570 --> 02:24.686
Wouldn't that keep the problem out?

02:24.688 --> 02:26.438
Maybe, or keep it in.

02:26.440 --> 02:29.157
Huh. Well, I left the bag behind.

02:29.159 --> 02:31.743
But when I got home, I got the rash.

02:31.745 --> 02:33.745
Well, they don't look too alarming.

02:33.747 --> 02:35.330
I'll do a scraping to test for scabies

02:35.332 --> 02:37.916
and give you a topical steroid cream.

02:37.918 --> 02:41.420
[Hums]

02:41.422 --> 02:44.089
Russel, is that you?

02:44.091 --> 02:45.957
A boy can't be in a good mood?

02:45.959 --> 02:47.626
Good mood?

02:47.628 --> 02:50.045
[Chuckles]
By the way, I love your shoes today.

02:50.047 --> 02:51.596
Okay, what's happening to you?

02:51.598 --> 02:52.848
Tell me while Hank is still here.

02:52.850 --> 02:55.166
Maybe he can save you.

02:59.522 --> 03:02.006
I'm taking a sabbatical
from Sutton & Chesterfield.

03:02.008 --> 03:04.008
What? Why?

03:04.010 --> 03:07.195
To do some private work
for a major client,

03:07.197 --> 03:09.114
a client I'm hoping

03:09.116 --> 03:11.566
will place the winning bid
for our prehistoric treasure.

03:11.568 --> 03:13.118
Is this client in the Hamptons?

03:13.120 --> 03:15.904
This client is everywhere.

03:15.906 --> 03:18.907
The job will involve
a lot of exotic travel.

03:18.909 --> 03:20.742
Sorry. I can't say more.

03:20.744 --> 03:23.528
I'm really happy for you, Russel.

03:23.530 --> 03:25.363
And I know my internship
is ending anyway,

03:25.365 --> 03:30.001
but I'm really gonna miss
working with you,

03:30.003 --> 03:31.636
especially the version of you
I'm working with today.

03:31.638 --> 03:32.754
[Laughs]

03:50.273 --> 03:52.274
[Clears throat]

03:57.062 --> 03:58.897
Jeremiah.

04:00.666 --> 04:03.618
Do you wanna maybe talk
somewhere a little more private?

04:03.620 --> 04:06.171
I feel comfortable here.

04:06.173 --> 04:07.539
Besides, I don't expect
this conversation

04:07.541 --> 04:10.742
will take very long.

04:10.744 --> 04:13.845
[Exhales]

04:13.847 --> 04:14.846
You resigned?

04:14.848 --> 04:16.598
Was my letter ambiguous?

04:16.600 --> 04:18.517
No.

04:18.519 --> 04:20.218
The resignation was very clear.

04:20.220 --> 04:21.970
The reason was not though,

04:21.971 --> 04:24.723
to me or to Hank.

04:24.725 --> 04:27.309
But I have a theory.

04:27.311 --> 04:30.111
What is your theory?

04:30.113 --> 04:31.429
Divya overheard me telling Paige

04:31.431 --> 04:34.783
about your feelings for her.

04:44.043 --> 04:47.779
Is that a good theory?

04:47.781 --> 04:49.080
Divya knows.
[Sighs]

04:49.082 --> 04:50.615
I'm sorry.

04:50.617 --> 04:52.801
I'm so sorry I broke your trust.

04:52.803 --> 04:54.553
Evan, I'm not upset with you.

04:54.555 --> 04:59.758
Um, that... that's not
the reason that I resigned.

04:59.760 --> 05:02.310
Then why did you?

05:02.312 --> 05:03.428
[Sighs]

05:03.430 --> 05:07.065
Hey. Take a photo of me doing this.

05:07.067 --> 05:08.967
Doing what?
[Laughs]

05:08.969 --> 05:10.518
Okay.

05:15.324 --> 05:16.741
[Laughs]

05:16.743 --> 05:18.977
Ow!

05:18.979 --> 05:21.112
Oh, my God. Are you okay?

05:21.114 --> 05:23.198
- He bit me.
- She.

05:23.200 --> 05:25.149
What happened?

05:25.151 --> 05:27.202
Russel said
the ancient skeleton bit him.

05:27.204 --> 05:29.170
Did her teeth
really need to be that sharp?

05:29.172 --> 05:30.538
What did she used to eat?

05:30.540 --> 05:32.156
Other dinosaurs.

05:32.158 --> 05:33.592
Hope you didn't break any bones.

05:33.594 --> 05:36.294
No, I'm fine. It's just a cut.

05:36.296 --> 05:37.762
I meant Emma's bones.

05:37.764 --> 05:39.214
I grazed her foot.

05:39.216 --> 05:41.666
Believe me, it hurt me
more than it hurt her.

05:41.668 --> 05:42.801
Okay, let me take a look, Russel.

05:42.803 --> 05:44.135
I'm telling you, she bit me.

05:44.137 --> 05:45.503
Well, in fairness to Emma,

05:45.505 --> 05:46.888
she hasn't eaten in 65 million years.

05:46.890 --> 05:48.106
She's probably worked up an appetite.

05:48.108 --> 05:51.860
[Laughs]
Really, Monique, I'm fine.

05:51.862 --> 05:54.779
You worried about Emma's foot?

05:54.781 --> 05:57.399
Maybe I can help you with that.

06:02.354 --> 06:04.823
Hey. What are you doing here?

06:04.825 --> 06:07.025
[Sighs]
We gotta talk.

06:16.869 --> 06:19.037
Hey. Thanks for coming down.

06:19.039 --> 06:21.706
Mm-hmm. What can I do for you?

06:21.708 --> 06:23.758
So I heard you resigned because of me.

06:23.760 --> 06:26.177
Yes.

06:26.179 --> 06:27.429
Sorry that wasn't more clear.

06:27.431 --> 06:30.265
Look, what happened wasn't your fault.

06:30.267 --> 06:31.316
It had to do...

06:31.318 --> 06:33.068
it seems I'm still being vague.

06:33.070 --> 06:36.688
I don't feel guilty. I feel angry.

06:36.690 --> 06:40.325
You came to me because you knew
you could manipulate me.

06:40.327 --> 06:42.027
When I suggested alternatives
to what you wanted,

06:42.029 --> 06:43.411
you deflected them.

06:43.413 --> 06:46.414
When I chose not to serve
your expectations,

06:46.416 --> 06:49.501
you went behind my back.

06:49.503 --> 06:52.236
You took advantage of me

06:52.238 --> 06:55.040
'cause you knew I respected you.

06:55.042 --> 06:58.343
And you didn't respect me back.

07:00.346 --> 07:04.132
That's why I'm angry.

07:08.521 --> 07:09.804
Okay, sorry, I should get back to work.

07:09.806 --> 07:11.940
Good-bye, Dr. Lawson.

