07:40.904 --> 07:43.605
- Just give me one sec, guys
- Oh, sure.

07:43.607 --> 07:46.208
What are you doing?

07:46.210 --> 07:49.245
Um, I'm just...
hold on for one second, okay?

07:49.247 --> 07:51.380
[Sighs]
Evan, we're already late.

07:51.382 --> 07:54.050
I know. It's... it's just 'cause
you changed outfits twice.

07:54.052 --> 07:55.551
Well, you were answering tweets.

07:55.553 --> 07:58.888
Leaving no time for emails, so...

08:00.390 --> 08:01.674
- Sir?
- No, ju...

08:01.676 --> 08:02.892
just...

08:02.894 --> 08:04.844
Babe, this is getting embarrassing.

08:04.846 --> 08:06.479
I know.

08:06.481 --> 08:07.796
Look, I promised Stu my first
order of business would be

08:07.798 --> 08:08.931
to help him build a second floor
at Chewy's, all right?

08:08.933 --> 08:10.632
And you have to build it tonight?

08:10.634 --> 08:12.735
No, I... I intend to be a politician

08:12.737 --> 08:13.769
who keeps his promises.

08:13.771 --> 08:15.604
And I intend to be a party guest

08:15.606 --> 08:17.189
who actually goes inside the party.

08:17.191 --> 08:20.993
Right, but... but...
[Sighs]

08:20.995 --> 08:22.978
Thank you, ma'am.

08:25.332 --> 08:27.366
Thank you so much for meeting me.

08:27.368 --> 08:29.201
I know Hankmed's been very busy lately.

08:29.203 --> 08:30.836
The end of the summer's always crazy.

08:30.838 --> 08:33.039
But also, you've kept the trains running

08:33.041 --> 08:34.840
with Hank preoccupied.

08:34.842 --> 08:36.708
I was just doing my job.

08:36.711 --> 08:38.659
It's Hank's practice.

08:38.662 --> 08:41.797
Divya, I think
you are enormously talented.

08:41.799 --> 08:43.849
After all, you were
my first impression of Hankmed.

08:43.851 --> 08:45.434
Gosh, that seems like ages ago.

08:45.436 --> 08:47.970
I think it's time for you
to have more responsibility

08:47.972 --> 08:49.972
and a higher profile within Symphony.

08:49.974 --> 08:52.475
I am sure that I have
all the responsibility

08:52.477 --> 08:54.060
that I can handle right now.

08:54.062 --> 08:57.530
Oh, well, how do you feel
about running a department?

08:57.532 --> 09:00.516
On top of my Hankmed duties.

09:00.518 --> 09:01.784
No.

09:01.786 --> 09:03.869
No, it would be a full-time position

09:03.871 --> 09:08.207
under one consolidated
concierge practice.

09:08.209 --> 09:10.459
Oh, my God. Are you firing Hank?

09:10.461 --> 09:11.860
Okay. Let me explain how...

09:11.862 --> 09:13.195
Don't bother.

09:13.197 --> 09:16.499
This conversation just ended.

09:20.370 --> 09:23.339
[Upbeat music]

09:23.341 --> 09:23.841
â™ª

09:31.933 --> 09:33.265
[Indistinct chatter]

09:33.267 --> 09:34.400
She bit me.
[Laughter]

09:34.402 --> 09:36.185
So Paige, tell me.

09:36.187 --> 09:38.354
You must be learning so much
from Russel.

09:38.356 --> 09:39.989
He is our most talented specialist.

09:39.991 --> 09:42.491
He's become a mentor, a great one.

09:42.493 --> 09:44.910
Ooh, look, I see a client.
Kisses, Paige.

09:44.912 --> 09:46.529
Your councilship.

09:46.531 --> 09:48.781
Kisses.

09:52.085 --> 09:54.954
- So this is fun.
- Yeah.

09:56.673 --> 09:59.041
- How long do you wanna stay?
- We just got here.

09:59.043 --> 10:00.759
- Right.
- Paige?

10:00.761 --> 10:03.129
- Hi.
- Hi.

10:03.131 --> 10:05.881
- Evan, so glad you could come.
- Thank you.

10:05.883 --> 10:07.249
Any good gossip from Kristof?

10:07.251 --> 10:09.518
He's such a yentamouth.
[Both laugh]

10:09.520 --> 10:10.970
Well, he was yenting about how you are

10:10.972 --> 10:12.188
the most talented specialist here.

10:12.190 --> 10:14.590
Don't be naive, Paige.

10:14.592 --> 10:15.858
He's heard about my sabbatical.

10:15.860 --> 10:17.359
So?

10:17.361 --> 10:19.061
He knows my fall residency
in our Paris office

10:19.063 --> 10:20.279
is up for grabs.

10:20.281 --> 10:21.981
So why is he sucking up to you?

10:21.983 --> 10:24.150
They asked me to pick my replacement.

10:24.152 --> 10:26.986
So are you two legal yet

10:26.988 --> 10:28.404
or what?
[Laughs]

10:28.406 --> 10:29.738
We just have to sign the paperwork.

10:29.740 --> 10:32.291
Yeah, and then repeat our vows
for the judge.

10:32.293 --> 10:33.542
But we had to cancel our appointment

10:33.544 --> 10:35.127
because we needed to vacate Shadow Pond.

10:35.129 --> 10:36.412
Mm-hmm.

10:36.414 --> 10:38.497
Huh. Another Hungarian psycho at large?

10:38.499 --> 10:40.449
No, Boris is in town for the weekend.

10:40.451 --> 10:41.500
But we can move back in once he leaves.

10:41.502 --> 10:44.720
Until we have to vacate again.

10:44.722 --> 10:46.055
The price of not having our own home.

10:46.057 --> 10:48.140
She keeps bringing it up. It's so funny.

10:48.142 --> 10:50.626
Not really.

10:50.628 --> 10:52.761
How comfortable for me.
Anyone need a drink?

10:52.763 --> 10:54.480
- No, I'm good.
- I'm all right.

10:54.482 --> 10:56.798
So do I.

11:04.241 --> 11:05.441
[Baby cries]

11:05.443 --> 11:07.026
He's learning
how to use that stethoscope

11:07.028 --> 11:08.911
faster than I did.

11:08.913 --> 11:10.312
Do you think Carlos will ask

11:10.314 --> 11:11.813
to see her again in six months?

11:11.815 --> 11:14.333
[Laughs]

11:14.335 --> 11:17.286
So Marisa found
a real clinical trial for you

11:17.288 --> 11:19.371
while planning a fake one for Milos?

11:19.373 --> 11:22.291
- Yep.
- Nothing shocks me anymore.

11:22.293 --> 11:24.493
I appreciate the irony, believe me,

11:24.495 --> 11:26.095
and the good fortune.

11:26.097 --> 11:27.963
I have not yet been cleared though

11:27.965 --> 11:30.332
to begin my treatment.

11:30.334 --> 11:31.500
Well, I'll rush the blood

11:31.502 --> 11:32.334
and have everything ready tomorrow.

11:32.336 --> 11:33.719
Thank you, Hank.

11:33.721 --> 11:35.688
The exam isn't the only reason
I called you though.

11:35.690 --> 11:38.557
Does Carlos want a job at Hankmed?

11:38.559 --> 11:42.344
Perhaps.
[Sighs]

11:42.346 --> 11:44.063
<i>Mi amor.</i>

11:45.532 --> 11:48.484
I have decided to take stock

11:48.486 --> 11:52.288
of my properties and assets...

11:52.290 --> 11:55.324
And begin to divest them.

11:55.326 --> 11:57.910
Wow. That sounds like a big step.

11:57.912 --> 11:59.295
It is.

11:59.297 --> 12:01.630
But after all the events
of this past year,

12:01.632 --> 12:03.031
it's time to leave the past behind

12:03.033 --> 12:04.800
and focus on the future.

12:04.802 --> 12:08.671
I want to simplify my life, Hank.

12:08.673 --> 12:10.172
I understand the way you feel.

12:10.174 --> 12:13.892
The chief investigator
of the clinical trial agreed

12:13.894 --> 12:15.844
I would be able to travel as necessary

12:15.846 --> 12:17.596
to take care of everything.

12:17.598 --> 12:19.881
If there is continuity of care.

12:19.883 --> 12:21.900
Yes.

12:21.902 --> 12:23.736
I volunteered,

12:23.738 --> 12:27.439
but family members are not
permitted to provide care.

12:27.441 --> 12:29.525
- Aha.
- So...

12:29.527 --> 12:32.194
Guys, I'm flattered. Truly, I am, but...

12:32.196 --> 12:33.412
Ah, you see? I told you.

12:33.414 --> 12:35.164
You can't take Hank out of Hankmed

12:35.166 --> 12:37.249
and drag him from Paris to Beijing

12:37.251 --> 12:39.585
to Sydney to Moscow.

12:39.587 --> 12:42.204
But I'm happy to help find someone else.

12:42.206 --> 12:43.372
It's not necessary.

12:43.374 --> 12:45.174
We already have a few candidates,

12:45.176 --> 12:47.626
not as universally loved
and trusted as you.

12:47.628 --> 12:49.345
Ah, it's not always so universal.

12:49.347 --> 12:51.847
But still, I can't leave my practice.

12:51.849 --> 12:53.849
You sure?

12:53.851 --> 12:57.636
I'm... I'm sorry, Boris.

12:57.638 --> 13:00.556
No apology necessary, Hank.

13:00.558 --> 13:02.808
I can't expect you
to complicate your life

13:02.810 --> 13:06.094
so that I may simplify mine,

13:06.096 --> 13:09.648
but it was worth a try.

13:18.792 --> 13:20.042
This is a new one for me.

13:20.044 --> 13:21.660
For Emma too.

13:21.662 --> 13:25.614
Doesn't really believe
in going to the doctor.

13:25.616 --> 13:28.133
No internal fracture.
[Sighs]

13:28.135 --> 13:29.418
That's great news.

13:29.420 --> 13:31.453
Emma should still fetch top dollar

13:31.455 --> 13:34.173
for the people of Mongolia.

13:34.175 --> 13:36.725
- Yeah, she should.
- Everything okay?

13:36.727 --> 13:38.794
Nah, you don't wanna hear
about my travails

13:38.796 --> 13:39.845
in the dinosaur business.

13:39.847 --> 13:41.013
Actually, I'd love to.

13:41.015 --> 13:42.431
I'm fascinated by what you do.

13:42.433 --> 13:45.484
Well, it's not quite
<i>Jurassic Park,</i> but...

13:45.486 --> 13:47.469
When I started working with dinosaurs,

13:47.471 --> 13:48.904
bone diggers were thieves,

13:48.906 --> 13:51.740
selling to the richest patron
they could find.

13:51.742 --> 13:55.811
I don't really believe
in that kind of paleontology.

13:55.813 --> 13:57.780
These government officials,

13:57.782 --> 13:59.248
oh, they promised
that the profits will go

13:59.250 --> 14:01.667
towards financing
a world-class museum, but...

14:01.669 --> 14:02.918
Now you're having doubts.

14:02.920 --> 14:05.037
I'm doubting whether these particular

14:05.039 --> 14:06.538
Mongolian officials actually serve

14:06.540 --> 14:08.624
the Mongolian people.

14:08.626 --> 14:10.292
What, you think they'll pocket the cash?

14:10.294 --> 14:12.928
Well, the cash seemed
to skip over the museum

14:12.930 --> 14:15.681
on our last venture.

14:15.683 --> 14:16.998
I just believe artifacts like this

14:17.000 --> 14:19.601
should be available for everyone to see,

14:19.603 --> 14:22.271
not just the mega-rich collectors.

14:22.273 --> 14:24.056
[Sighs]
Monique?

14:24.058 --> 14:25.607
Are you... are you feeling okay?

14:25.609 --> 14:27.893
Yeah, I'm just a bit tired and sore.

14:27.895 --> 14:30.863
The scraping from your rash
was negative for scabies.

14:30.865 --> 14:34.650
Mm.
[Thermometer beeps]

14:34.652 --> 14:36.869
But now you have a fever.

14:36.871 --> 14:39.405
- Well, what does that mean?
- Probably an infection.

14:39.407 --> 14:41.073
And with your travel,
it could be anything.

14:41.075 --> 14:43.692
- Like what?
- Maybe just a virus.

14:43.694 --> 14:46.044
But it could be tularemia,
which is a bacteria

14:46.046 --> 14:47.546
you can get from digging in dirt.

14:47.548 --> 14:49.248
Oh, well, what are the symptoms?

14:49.250 --> 14:51.383
Fever, lethargy, and skin lesions.

14:51.385 --> 14:53.034
Oh.
[Laughs]

14:53.036 --> 14:54.035
Well, that sounds
like a pretty good guess.

14:54.037 --> 14:55.337
[Laughs]

14:55.339 --> 14:56.972
I'll give you prophylactic antibiotics

14:56.974 --> 14:58.590
to be safe, but I wanna do a blood draw

14:58.592 --> 14:59.725
and a chest X-ray.

14:59.727 --> 15:01.977
- Okay.
- Okay, good.

15:08.184 --> 15:10.269
He's returning constituent emails.

15:10.271 --> 15:13.105
He's been a good sport.
This clearly isn't his scene.

15:13.107 --> 15:17.025
Well, it is mine, but we're leaving.

15:17.027 --> 15:18.160
Before you go, I want your opinion

15:18.162 --> 15:19.611
on choosing my Paris replacement.

15:19.613 --> 15:21.697
Oh, okay.

15:21.699 --> 15:23.332
You have a front-runner in mind?

15:23.334 --> 15:24.950
I do.

15:24.952 --> 15:27.419
And do you have any concerns
about that person?

15:27.421 --> 15:29.955
Just two:

15:29.957 --> 15:32.591
Whether she'd be so cheerful,
she'd force the French to smile,

15:32.593 --> 15:36.178
and whether she could take
a semester off from Parsons

15:36.180 --> 15:37.546
for the job of a lifetime.

15:37.548 --> 15:39.214
You're being serious.

15:39.216 --> 15:41.216
You're the best intern I've ever had.

15:41.218 --> 15:43.084
[Laughs]

15:43.086 --> 15:44.686
I respect you.

15:44.688 --> 15:46.188
I trust you.

15:46.190 --> 15:47.806
Unless you wanna lobby for Kristof,

15:47.808 --> 15:48.857
- who's the runner-up.
- No.

15:48.859 --> 15:52.611
No, no.
[Laughs]

15:52.613 --> 15:54.146
What's going on over here?

15:54.148 --> 15:56.231
Oh, don't sweat it. She's not my type.

15:56.233 --> 15:57.900
- What'd I miss?
- Oh, that.

15:57.902 --> 16:01.119
You and your wife are going
to Paris for a few months.

16:01.121 --> 16:02.488
Perfect timing too.

16:02.490 --> 16:05.240
Nothing like the most
passionate city on earth

16:05.242 --> 16:07.793
to rekindle a troubled romance.

16:13.249 --> 16:14.650
Hmm.

16:18.675 --> 16:21.426
Where are all of Divya's boxes
supposed to go?

16:21.428 --> 16:23.628
Um, anything else you told Russel?

16:23.630 --> 16:26.130
Oh, you don't discuss our
relationship with other people?

16:26.132 --> 16:29.350
You told him it's...
what was the word, "troubled"?

16:29.352 --> 16:31.936
Oh. How unfair of me.

16:31.938 --> 16:33.938
Clearly, this marriage
is just killing it.

16:33.940 --> 16:36.107
Okay, Paige, Paige.

16:36.109 --> 16:38.109
It may not be perfect, but it's ours.

16:38.111 --> 16:39.760
So if you wanna discuss
its imperfections,

16:39.762 --> 16:42.113
please do it with me, okay?

16:42.115 --> 16:44.148
I'm glad Russel said it.

16:44.150 --> 16:45.817
At least it got us
talking about our issues

16:45.819 --> 16:46.868
instead of avoiding them.

16:46.870 --> 16:47.935
What are you talking about?

16:47.937 --> 16:49.070
We haven't been avoiding them at all.

16:49.072 --> 16:50.488
We've been really busy this summer.

16:50.490 --> 16:51.739
Both of us have.

16:51.741 --> 16:53.908
Which is why we should go to Paris.

16:53.910 --> 16:55.326
What's it gonna look like

16:55.328 --> 16:57.212
if I go gallivanting off to Europe

16:57.214 --> 16:58.463
right after getting elected?

16:58.465 --> 17:01.949
Might look like you care about us.

17:01.951 --> 17:04.085
I do care. I care so much.

17:04.087 --> 17:06.287
But you're asking me to...

17:06.289 --> 17:08.089
what, you want me to leave my job

17:08.090 --> 17:09.840
and all my responsibilities behind,

17:09.843 --> 17:12.393
so I can run off to Paris for your job?

17:12.395 --> 17:13.645
I told you,

17:13.646 --> 17:16.631
I... I made promises that I have to keep.

17:20.469 --> 17:21.903
I have to go.

17:21.905 --> 17:24.805
I have to stay.

17:26.308 --> 17:28.276
Thanks for meeting with us.

17:28.278 --> 17:30.078
Course. What are we meeting about?

17:30.080 --> 17:32.080
The fact that you're trying
to replace him.

17:32.082 --> 17:34.332
Divya told you about our chat.

17:34.334 --> 17:36.034
She might have mentioned it, yeah.

17:36.036 --> 17:39.654
Hank, nothing has been
officially decided yet,

17:39.656 --> 17:42.090
but you did put us in a tough spot.

17:42.092 --> 17:43.291
Now the lawyers are trying to figure out

17:43.293 --> 17:44.792
the best course of action.

17:44.794 --> 17:46.878
And until then,
I need to explore my options.

17:46.880 --> 17:48.346
What are the lawyers figuring out?

17:48.348 --> 17:49.931
My client didn't do anything wrong.

17:49.933 --> 17:52.216
He violated his morals clause.

17:52.218 --> 17:55.053
My contract has a morals clause?

17:55.055 --> 17:56.271
I figured with you,

17:56.273 --> 17:57.338
it was the last thing
I had to worry about.

17:57.340 --> 17:58.673
Right, well, you and Shelby

17:58.675 --> 17:59.857
had more important things to agree on.

17:59.859 --> 18:01.842
Hank, I understand that you're angry,

18:01.844 --> 18:03.027
and I'm angry too.

18:03.029 --> 18:05.029
I went to the mat for you,

18:05.031 --> 18:07.282
never expecting that mat
to be out on a limb.

18:07.284 --> 18:08.399
And now my ass is on the line.

18:08.401 --> 18:09.817
So you're scrambling to cover it,

18:09.819 --> 18:11.819
which must be tough,
what with it being on the line

18:11.821 --> 18:13.705
on the mat on the limb.
Did I get that right?

18:13.707 --> 18:15.657
This is about <i>your</i> impropriety.

18:15.659 --> 18:17.158
The appearance of impropriety.

18:17.160 --> 18:18.493
I was treating pain,

18:18.495 --> 18:21.028
and I never compromised
my ability to do my job.

18:21.030 --> 18:23.915
So the hospital administration
is being naive and reactionary.

18:23.917 --> 18:25.466
Just curious, is that what happened

18:25.468 --> 18:26.968
back at Brooklyn Heights Mercy Hospital

18:26.970 --> 18:28.836
before you moved to the Hamptons?

18:28.838 --> 18:31.923
[Exhales]

18:31.925 --> 18:34.092
When you said Symphony was different,

18:34.094 --> 18:35.760
that they put patients first,

18:35.762 --> 18:37.979
you might have also mentioned
that they put doctors last.

18:37.981 --> 18:39.931
You wanna let me go? That's fine.

18:39.933 --> 18:42.266
I'll go back to practicing
the way I did before,

18:42.268 --> 18:43.818
and we'll all be happier.

18:43.820 --> 18:45.687
That'd be nice, but unfortunately,

18:45.689 --> 18:48.189
it's not that simple.

18:48.191 --> 18:50.158
Your contract also has
a non-compete clause.

18:50.160 --> 18:53.244
So you're welcome to go back
to where you were

18:53.246 --> 18:55.830
as long as it's not
within 200 miles of here.

18:58.834 --> 19:02.170
[Device beeps]

19:02.172 --> 19:03.504
Okay.

19:03.506 --> 19:05.039
Russel.

19:05.041 --> 19:06.741
Your nervousness is making me nervous.

19:06.743 --> 19:08.092
You'd be crazy <i>not</i> to be nervous.

19:08.094 --> 19:10.044
Why should we be nervous?

19:10.046 --> 19:11.379
His private client is coming to visit,

19:11.381 --> 19:13.431
the one we hope wins Emma
at the auction.

19:13.433 --> 19:14.549
Oh.

19:14.551 --> 19:15.550
It's not easy marketing a dinosaur.

19:15.552 --> 19:16.634
[Chuckles]

19:16.636 --> 19:19.470
Hey. How did the meeting go?

19:19.472 --> 19:20.972
Not well.

19:20.974 --> 19:23.274
- Sorry to hear that.
- How's it going here?

19:23.276 --> 19:25.610
Russel had too much coffee.

19:25.612 --> 19:27.061
What makes you say that?

19:27.063 --> 19:29.197
[Groans]
I think I've had too much coffee.

19:29.199 --> 19:30.598
Huh.

19:30.600 --> 19:33.067
My client is very serious
about anonymity.

19:33.069 --> 19:36.120
Any chance we can complete
this exam expeditiously?

19:36.122 --> 19:37.205
We rush all our exams.

19:37.207 --> 19:41.042
That's why our patients are so healthy.

19:41.044 --> 19:42.660
Monique, let me have a look.

19:42.662 --> 19:44.912
[Clears throat]

19:44.914 --> 19:46.798
Yeah, your rash is starting to clear up.

19:46.800 --> 19:49.300
No fever,
which means it's not tularemia.

19:49.302 --> 19:50.752
But we're still not sure what it is.

19:50.754 --> 19:52.053
I'm just glad it's not soil.

19:52.055 --> 19:54.305
I love soil,
or at least what I find in it.

19:54.307 --> 19:56.507
For someone who spends
so much time in dirt,

19:56.509 --> 19:57.508
you clean up real nice.

19:57.510 --> 19:58.976
Oh. Thanks.

19:58.978 --> 20:01.062
Well, it's no easy chore.

20:01.064 --> 20:02.230
I have the most overworked loofah

20:02.232 --> 20:05.600
in the Western hemisphere.

20:05.602 --> 20:07.101
Sorry.

20:07.103 --> 20:08.770
No. Monique, can I see your back?

20:08.772 --> 20:11.906
Um, sure.

20:11.908 --> 20:14.692
[Zipper unzips]

20:14.694 --> 20:16.828
Yep.

20:16.830 --> 20:18.863
- Do you scrub right here?
- No.

20:18.865 --> 20:20.998
I'd need trenching equipment
to get to that area.

20:21.000 --> 20:24.285
Monique, how old
is your overworked loofah?

20:24.287 --> 20:26.587
Uh, I don't know.

20:26.589 --> 20:29.791
I mean, it's got quite
a few miles on it, I'm sure.

20:29.793 --> 20:32.176
- Why?
- Because it caused your rash.

20:32.178 --> 20:33.928
Pseudomonas folliculitis.

20:33.930 --> 20:37.265
Sorry, that species is
outside of my biological domain.

20:37.267 --> 20:39.434
It's an infection of the hair follicles

20:39.436 --> 20:42.303
due to bacteria that contaminate
bathing products.

20:42.305 --> 20:45.022
Oh. Prescription.

20:45.024 --> 20:46.474
[Laughs]
New loofah.

20:46.476 --> 20:50.194
Where should I put
these giant dinosaur eggs?

20:50.196 --> 20:51.979
Uh, just over on that side table.

20:51.981 --> 20:55.450
They may be giant,
but Emma still had it easy.

20:55.452 --> 20:56.534
You can hold the nest if you like.

20:56.536 --> 20:59.287
It's just a plaster reproduction.

20:59.289 --> 21:00.988
It's light. Hmm.

21:00.990 --> 21:03.357
[Gasps]

21:03.359 --> 21:05.860
Divya, what's wrong?

21:05.862 --> 21:08.463
I... I don't know.

21:08.465 --> 21:11.332
[Groans]

21:18.672 --> 21:20.021
Obviously, you've been monitoring it.

21:20.023 --> 21:21.606
The intrauterine septum? Yeah.

21:21.608 --> 21:23.141
Since my first ultrasound.

21:23.143 --> 21:24.443
We knew it could cause trouble.

21:24.445 --> 21:25.510
But it hasn't.

21:25.512 --> 21:28.447
Until now.

21:28.449 --> 21:30.282
Until now.

21:30.284 --> 21:31.700
A little English, please?

21:31.702 --> 21:32.951
For all the non-medical loved ones.

21:32.953 --> 21:34.369
Uh, there's a wedge-shaped partition

21:34.371 --> 21:35.454
in her uterine cavity.

21:35.456 --> 21:36.872
That's plenty of English. Thanks.

21:36.874 --> 21:38.123
Okay.

21:38.125 --> 21:41.409
I am seeing something new here.

21:44.130 --> 21:45.914
A sub-chorionic hemorrhage.

21:45.916 --> 21:47.749
Right behind the placenta.

21:47.751 --> 21:49.134
But I don't have any bleeding...

21:49.136 --> 21:52.587
[Groans]
Divya.

21:52.589 --> 21:54.473
The good news is
that it's not an abruption.

21:54.475 --> 21:56.708
Divya, I'll give you Tylenol
for the pain.

21:56.710 --> 22:00.712
But the key is rest
until the cramps subside.

22:00.714 --> 22:03.715
- We'll take turns visiting.
- Yeah.

22:06.402 --> 22:08.320
Jeremiah.

22:08.322 --> 22:10.555
Uh, may I...

22:10.557 --> 22:15.193
Of course. Jeremiah, please come in.

22:15.195 --> 22:16.695
How did you know?

22:16.697 --> 22:18.997
Evan.

22:18.999 --> 22:19.948
Hmm.

22:19.950 --> 22:23.034
Thank you for the call.

22:23.036 --> 22:25.337
Uh, guys, let's let Jeremiah visit.

22:25.339 --> 22:28.039
Yeah.

22:28.041 --> 22:31.593
Bye.

22:36.265 --> 22:37.682
[Sighs]

22:37.684 --> 22:39.935
[Door closes]

22:39.937 --> 22:43.054
How are you feeling?
[Sighs]

22:43.056 --> 22:46.424
A bit calmer now.

22:46.426 --> 22:48.026
How about you?

22:48.028 --> 22:50.762
[Sighs]

22:59.655 --> 23:01.156
It seems we have a lot to discuss

23:01.158 --> 23:03.542
after you're discharged.

23:03.544 --> 23:05.660
We can discuss it now,

23:05.662 --> 23:08.213
or we can just talk
about something else.

23:08.215 --> 23:10.382
It's entirely up to you.

23:13.118 --> 23:14.636
[Sighs]

23:26.298 --> 23:29.801
Joining Hankmed was a very
difficult adjustment for me.

23:34.574 --> 23:36.992
But you made it so much easier

23:36.994 --> 23:39.411
with your kindness

23:39.413 --> 23:41.913
and your compassion.

23:44.116 --> 23:46.167
In retrospect,

23:46.169 --> 23:49.921
I believe that's when my feelings began.

23:49.923 --> 23:52.924
I just never found the strength
to tell you.

23:55.160 --> 23:57.829
Yeah, you did.

23:57.831 --> 23:59.831
You found it today.

24:12.895 --> 24:13.895
How's she doing?

24:13.897 --> 24:15.780
She's resting.

24:17.817 --> 24:21.236
So I thought about what you said.

24:22.521 --> 24:23.788
It was manipulative

24:23.790 --> 24:25.040
to ask you to prescribe those meds

24:25.042 --> 24:28.460
and then disregard your advice.

24:28.462 --> 24:30.578
I needed to prove
that I could shoulder the burden

24:30.580 --> 24:32.797
all on my own.

24:32.799 --> 24:34.132
I needed to prove it to Hankmed,

24:34.134 --> 24:38.036
to our patients, to myself.

24:38.038 --> 24:40.371
But that was my problem,

24:40.373 --> 24:42.307
and I made it yours.

24:42.309 --> 24:44.893
I just... I didn't treat you

24:44.895 --> 24:47.979
with the respect you deserve.

24:47.981 --> 24:51.816
But I do respect you, Jeremiah.

24:51.818 --> 24:53.068
I mean, since you came here,

24:53.070 --> 24:56.438
you've met every challenge you've faced.

24:58.908 --> 25:03.161
And I'm very sorry
that I was one of them.

25:05.164 --> 25:08.750
I hope you'll come back

25:08.752 --> 25:11.736
because we need you.

25:14.623 --> 25:16.791
I need you.

25:18.911 --> 25:20.745
I accept your apology.

25:20.747 --> 25:24.182
And thank you for the explanation.

25:24.184 --> 25:26.968
I wanted to please you,

25:26.970 --> 25:29.420
and I compromised my medical
judgment because of that

25:29.422 --> 25:32.607
and because of insecurities

25:32.609 --> 25:37.445
about other issues in my life.

25:37.447 --> 25:41.866
So I... I'm partly responsible.

25:41.868 --> 25:46.287
But I mustn't risk
repeating those errors.

25:46.289 --> 25:48.289
So...

25:50.960 --> 25:54.612
I can't work with you ever again.

26:09.895 --> 26:11.462
She's hanging us out to dry.

26:11.464 --> 26:15.066
Typical corporate suit.
Saving her own ass.

26:15.068 --> 26:17.519
Mm. All right.

26:17.521 --> 26:19.404
[Snaps fingers]
So what's our move?

26:19.406 --> 26:21.272
Well, we need her back in our corner.

26:21.274 --> 26:23.324
I don't want her near our corner.

26:23.326 --> 26:24.642
No, Hank, we have to fight
the non-compete.

26:24.644 --> 26:26.144
This is our livelihood.

26:26.146 --> 26:27.862
This is more than that.
This is personal.

26:27.864 --> 26:29.864
This is about defending yourself, Hank.

26:29.866 --> 26:30.915
You are Hankmed.

26:30.917 --> 26:32.367
Hankmed is a team effort.

26:32.369 --> 26:33.785
Yeah, you can spare us the modesty, doc.

26:33.787 --> 26:35.086
It's not strategically
productive right now.

26:35.088 --> 26:36.621
Okay.

26:36.623 --> 26:38.206
Trusted by patients

26:38.208 --> 26:39.340
battling severe pain...

26:39.342 --> 26:41.159
pain that symphony's own doctors

26:41.161 --> 26:43.428
couldn't even diagnose.

26:43.430 --> 26:46.014
That's it. Evan, you're a genius.

26:46.016 --> 26:47.465
I'm with you so far.

26:47.467 --> 26:49.768
We threaten to countersue.

26:49.770 --> 26:51.803
Hamptons Heritage failed
to properly investigate

26:51.805 --> 26:53.388
Dr. Lawson's post-operative pain.

26:53.390 --> 26:55.690
No, no, it's not quite
that simple, Keller.

26:55.692 --> 26:57.175
We'll show them impro-fricking-priety.

26:57.177 --> 26:59.177
First, their own incompetence
causes my client

26:59.179 --> 27:00.562
prolonged pain and suffering.

27:00.564 --> 27:01.980
Then they discriminate against him

27:01.982 --> 27:03.398
for treating the very pain they caused.

27:03.400 --> 27:04.566
Ken, that's just not...

27:04.568 --> 27:05.900
We'll bring Shelby to her knees.

27:05.902 --> 27:07.068
Huh.

27:07.070 --> 27:08.236
I walked right into that one.

27:08.238 --> 27:10.238
So I love a good counterattack,

27:10.240 --> 27:11.689
but I'm a newly elected councilman.

27:11.691 --> 27:12.957
I can't be seen targeting

27:12.959 --> 27:14.459
the community hospital for annihilation.

27:14.461 --> 27:16.494
Yeah, nor can I as, you know, a doctor.

27:16.496 --> 27:18.413
I may not have caused
your problem, Hank,

27:18.415 --> 27:19.747
but I certainly made it worse.

27:19.749 --> 27:21.216
And that's not what you hired me to do.

27:21.218 --> 27:22.801
It's time for me to make this right.

27:22.803 --> 27:27.005
No, Ken, please,
just don't make anything right.

27:27.007 --> 27:28.423
[Sighs]

27:28.425 --> 27:29.891
[Knocking at door]

27:29.893 --> 27:32.393
Russel, I thought we were meeting here.

27:32.395 --> 27:35.230
<i>Je suis a votre porte.</i>

27:35.232 --> 27:38.733
Uh, I'm in for Paris.

27:38.735 --> 27:40.268
And I hope you know how much

27:40.270 --> 27:41.719
your confidence means to me.

27:41.721 --> 27:43.571
I... as you can tell, I'm brushing up on

27:43.573 --> 27:45.240
<i>mon francaise en ce moment.</i>

27:45.242 --> 27:46.891
[Footsteps approach]

27:46.893 --> 27:48.693
Russel, are you in there?

27:48.695 --> 27:51.913
[Groans]

27:51.915 --> 27:54.115
Russel?

27:59.475 --> 28:00.909
[Groaning]

28:00.911 --> 28:02.360
I also called 911.

28:02.362 --> 28:04.529
I know you're not supposed
to do anything for a seizure,

28:04.531 --> 28:05.664
but why won't it stop?

28:05.666 --> 28:07.115
[Panting]

28:07.117 --> 28:08.366
Because this isn't a seizure.

28:08.368 --> 28:10.285
He's making eye contact.
[Groans]

28:10.287 --> 28:12.037
- Russel, can you hear me?
- Help me.

28:12.039 --> 28:13.421
[Pants]

28:13.423 --> 28:15.006
I think he's experiencing

28:15.008 --> 28:17.208
somatic skeletal
neuromuscular dysfunction.

28:17.210 --> 28:19.761
[Groans]
Something poisoned him.

28:19.763 --> 28:21.129
[Sirens wail]
Wha...

28:21.131 --> 28:22.931
you think this is related to his cut?

28:22.933 --> 28:25.133
It's not a cut.

28:25.135 --> 28:27.502
I think this is a bite,
just not from a dinosaur,

28:27.504 --> 28:29.105
and he's having a reaction to the venom.

28:29.106 --> 28:30.855
[Groaning]

28:30.857 --> 28:32.607
In here.

28:32.609 --> 28:34.609
- Is there an antivenom?
- I'm gonna find out.

28:34.611 --> 28:36.478
- What can I do?
- Call poison control.

28:36.480 --> 28:37.779
They need to inspect Emma.

28:37.781 --> 28:39.531
We have to find and identify
the source of the bite

28:39.533 --> 28:40.899
to know what to administer.

28:40.901 --> 28:42.016
I'll go in the ambulance with him.

28:42.018 --> 28:43.818
- I'll meet them on site.
- Okay.

28:43.820 --> 28:45.904
And warn Monique to stay away.

28:45.906 --> 28:48.856
If something poisonous is hiding
inside her dinosaur,

28:48.858 --> 28:49.874
she could be next.

28:49.876 --> 28:51.209
- Right here, guys.
- Okay.

28:51.211 --> 28:52.794
- Let's lay it down right here.
- Got it.

28:52.796 --> 28:55.880
Monique? Monique, are you here?

28:57.166 --> 28:58.199
[Sighs]

29:06.475 --> 29:07.559
Paige.

29:07.561 --> 29:09.644
There you are. Oh, my God... wait.

29:09.646 --> 29:12.347
What are you doing here?

29:12.349 --> 29:13.848
Hank called me. I'm here to help.

29:13.850 --> 29:15.216
Help how?

29:15.218 --> 29:16.568
I'm not gonna let you
inside that thing's mouth.

29:16.570 --> 29:17.569
What if it's deadly or something?

29:17.571 --> 29:19.688
Well, then, Russel's dying.

29:19.690 --> 29:21.156
Look, one of us has to do this.

29:21.158 --> 29:24.693
Are you volunteering?

29:24.695 --> 29:25.744
I... I... wait, wait, wait, wait.
Just come down.

29:25.746 --> 29:29.664
Come down, come down.

29:29.666 --> 29:32.734
All right.

29:32.736 --> 29:36.871
Just make sure Hollywood
tells my story, okay?

29:36.873 --> 29:38.590
- I love you.
- Love you.

29:38.592 --> 29:41.743
Okay.

29:46.349 --> 29:50.185
- Wait.
- Oh, thank God.

29:50.187 --> 29:53.188
Take these.

29:53.190 --> 29:54.522
What am I supposed to do with these?

29:54.524 --> 29:57.359
You want me to moonwalk?

29:57.361 --> 30:00.228
It's better than nothing.

30:00.230 --> 30:02.480
Yeah, you're right.

30:03.866 --> 30:05.617
Very small.

30:05.619 --> 30:08.319
Grown men wear these?

30:08.321 --> 30:11.706
- Got that one on.
- Yeah.

30:11.708 --> 30:14.108
Eh.

30:14.110 --> 30:17.829
Do you need some help? Just... let's go.

30:19.215 --> 30:21.115
All right.

30:21.117 --> 30:22.417
Okay.

30:22.419 --> 30:23.418
- So can you just...
- I got it, I got it.

30:23.420 --> 30:24.803
Just don't look down.

30:24.805 --> 30:26.554
It's a little better
than looking up right now,

30:26.556 --> 30:28.056
but, uh...

30:33.128 --> 30:34.929
Oh, my God.
[Groans]

30:34.931 --> 30:36.431
Do you see anything in there?

30:36.433 --> 30:38.600
Only my life flashing before my eyes.

30:38.602 --> 30:41.469
But it's actually pretty dark.

30:43.022 --> 30:45.273
Actually, really dark. I can't...

30:45.275 --> 30:46.991
hey, I can't...

30:46.993 --> 30:49.494
it's just dark and terrifying.

30:49.496 --> 30:50.645
[Cell phone beeps]
Here.

30:50.647 --> 30:53.498
Here, here.

30:53.500 --> 30:54.949
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

30:54.951 --> 30:58.253
That's a good idea.

30:58.255 --> 31:00.538
So there we go. Now I can see.

31:00.540 --> 31:03.541
Uh, it's pretty bony.

31:04.927 --> 31:07.929
It smells funny in here.

31:07.931 --> 31:09.798
Oh, God! The tongue moved.

31:09.800 --> 31:12.717
What tongue?

31:12.719 --> 31:15.303
[Siren wails]

31:15.305 --> 31:16.888
Just hang on, Russel, okay?

31:16.890 --> 31:18.606
Just hang on. We're almost there.

31:18.608 --> 31:20.308
[Cell phone chimes]

31:20.310 --> 31:22.560
[Groans]

31:22.562 --> 31:24.195
It wasn't a bite that caused this.

31:24.197 --> 31:26.614
It was a sting, a scorpion sting.

31:26.616 --> 31:28.650
[Panting]

31:28.652 --> 31:31.352
[Siren wails]

31:39.161 --> 31:42.964
Hey, Boris.

31:42.966 --> 31:45.800
Oh.

31:45.802 --> 31:49.337
- Hank.
- Yeah.

31:49.339 --> 31:50.638
Good.

31:50.640 --> 31:52.039
How is Mr. Berger faring?

31:52.041 --> 31:53.758
He'll be fine. But how did you...

31:53.760 --> 31:57.378
Monique, you know Dr. Lawson.

31:57.380 --> 32:00.482
Hello, Monique.

32:00.484 --> 32:02.901
So you're the secret bidder.

32:02.903 --> 32:04.886
Russel was in the process of brokering

32:04.888 --> 32:07.822
our arrangement when he fell ill.

32:07.824 --> 32:09.390
Monique has been kind enough
to come here herself

32:09.392 --> 32:11.192
to finalize the details.

32:11.194 --> 32:12.944
So Russel will be accompanying you

32:12.946 --> 32:14.445
on your trip around the world.

32:14.447 --> 32:16.664
Uh, his expertise
is particularly well-suited

32:16.666 --> 32:19.367
for my current needs, as you know.

32:19.369 --> 32:21.536
That's if he's well enough to travel.

32:21.538 --> 32:24.572
He will be fine.

32:24.574 --> 32:27.041
I'm happy to see you so... at home.

32:27.043 --> 32:29.460
I have a lot to be thankful for.

32:29.462 --> 32:30.929
But that's not why you came. What...

32:30.931 --> 32:32.597
Your blood tests were normal.

32:32.599 --> 32:34.415
You'll be cleared for the trial.

32:34.417 --> 32:36.267
That's welcome news. Thank you, Hank.

32:36.269 --> 32:38.186
- Did you hear that?
- I did.

32:38.188 --> 32:39.721
Congrats on finding a buyer.

32:39.723 --> 32:41.856
Well, the sale won't be
officially settled

32:41.858 --> 32:43.090
until the auction.

32:43.092 --> 32:45.276
But if Boris submits the winning bid,

32:45.278 --> 32:46.928
we plan to donate Emma back

32:46.930 --> 32:48.863
to Mongolia's Museum of Natural History,

32:48.865 --> 32:51.199
where she belongs.

32:51.201 --> 32:52.317
So now all you have to do, Boris,

32:52.319 --> 32:53.368
is submit the winning bid

32:53.370 --> 32:55.537
for a priceless prehistoric treasure.

32:55.539 --> 32:58.540
I like my chances.

33:01.911 --> 33:04.212
I can release you
as soon as the cramping ceases,

33:04.214 --> 33:06.130
but you need to stay in bed.

33:06.132 --> 33:07.298
For how long?

33:07.300 --> 33:09.300
At least until your 27th week.

33:09.302 --> 33:10.752
You'll be on bed rest.

33:10.754 --> 33:13.555
No going to work, no going on vacation,

33:13.557 --> 33:15.006
no going to the mailbox.

33:15.008 --> 33:17.342
No going anywhere
that's farther than the fridge.

33:17.344 --> 33:19.477
How could I do that for a day,

33:19.479 --> 33:20.895
let alone for months?

33:20.897 --> 33:23.481
You'll need help.

33:24.817 --> 33:26.985
- Are you two...
- No.

33:26.987 --> 33:29.103
We're just friends.

33:29.105 --> 33:31.639
But we live together,

33:31.641 --> 33:33.641
and I'll be taking care of her.

33:33.643 --> 33:35.860
Well, there you go then.

33:35.862 --> 33:38.863
I'll see you before you leave.

33:44.203 --> 33:46.004
[Sighs]

33:46.006 --> 33:47.005
Can't let you do that.

33:47.007 --> 33:49.824
Why not?

33:49.826 --> 33:51.993
What about your research?

33:51.995 --> 33:55.213
I can conduct most of it from home.

33:55.215 --> 33:58.099
Still, I can't.

34:00.102 --> 34:03.054
We can't.

34:03.056 --> 34:07.609
Because you're worried I might
still be in love with you.

34:07.611 --> 34:08.693
[Sighs]

34:08.695 --> 34:11.813
I don't want to take advantage of...

34:11.815 --> 34:15.233
Well...
[Clears throat]

34:15.235 --> 34:17.485
Um, working in the lab, I've had time

34:17.487 --> 34:20.655
to think about things.

34:20.657 --> 34:23.741
I... I know you care about my feelings.

34:23.743 --> 34:27.295
Um, I... I realize

34:27.297 --> 34:31.299
you may even care too much.

34:31.301 --> 34:33.418
The way I feel about you has changed.

34:33.420 --> 34:36.004
Um, I've outgrown that

34:36.005 --> 34:38.973
the way I've outgrown the lab.

34:38.975 --> 34:42.560
But I haven't outgrown our friendship.

34:43.846 --> 34:46.931
So...

34:46.933 --> 34:49.600
Please be my friend,

34:49.601 --> 34:51.601
and let me be yours.

34:55.891 --> 34:58.242
[Sighs]

35:04.783 --> 35:07.702
[Knocks at door]

35:07.704 --> 35:09.570
- Hey.
- Hey.

35:09.572 --> 35:11.005
Nice job getting Russel to us.

35:11.007 --> 35:13.708
Nice job getting the antivenom
to Russel.

35:13.710 --> 35:17.712
A lot of hospitals
don't even stock it anymore.

35:17.714 --> 35:21.683
Hank, we decided not to
exercise the non-compete clause.

35:21.685 --> 35:23.968
Keller came to see you.

35:23.970 --> 35:27.522
He's a very persuasive lawyer
when he needs to be.

35:27.524 --> 35:30.558
You are free to practice locally.

35:30.560 --> 35:32.193
And we can keep the Hankmed name?

35:32.195 --> 35:34.529
Aw, it's all yours, I can assure you.

35:34.531 --> 35:37.264
Well, it seems like
our stock has dropped

35:37.266 --> 35:38.766
quite a bit since Symphony chased us

35:38.768 --> 35:40.368
all over the Hamptons
trying to acquire us.

35:40.370 --> 35:41.703
I don't think this is how any of us

35:41.705 --> 35:44.956
saw our investment playing out.

35:44.958 --> 35:46.824
But Symphony looks forward to seeing you

35:46.826 --> 35:51.445
whenever you bring your patients
into our hospital.

35:53.448 --> 35:55.633
Good-bye, Dr. Lawson.

36:14.764 --> 36:16.966
What, no lemon?

36:16.968 --> 36:17.967
That's funny.

36:17.969 --> 36:20.252
[Laughs]
Thank you.

36:20.254 --> 36:22.388
And for the tea too.

36:22.390 --> 36:24.356
But seriously, Jeremiah,
you can't wait on me

36:24.358 --> 36:25.641
hand and foot.

36:25.643 --> 36:26.809
Uh, I don't intend to hover.

36:26.811 --> 36:28.594
I understand that can become vexing.

36:28.596 --> 36:30.229
I'll let you know if it does.

36:30.231 --> 36:34.466
But so far, I've quite enjoyed it.

36:34.468 --> 36:36.318
Hey.

36:36.320 --> 36:37.987
Hope you don't mind the intrusion.

36:37.989 --> 36:39.705
I just... I didn't want Divya
to have to get up

36:39.707 --> 36:41.106
to get the door if she was alone.

36:41.108 --> 36:44.126
No problem. She's not alone.

36:44.128 --> 36:46.612
Right.

36:46.614 --> 36:49.164
So what have you got for me there?

36:49.166 --> 36:51.300
I know it's a little early, but...

36:51.302 --> 36:54.119
Thank you for not saying "premature."

36:54.121 --> 36:55.120
I love it.

36:55.122 --> 36:56.839
But for now, it'll be mine.

36:56.841 --> 36:58.173
All right.

36:58.175 --> 36:59.808
- You feeling better?
- I am.

36:59.810 --> 37:01.343
Is she telling the truth?

37:01.345 --> 37:03.846
In my experience,
Divya is a truthful person.

37:03.848 --> 37:06.465
Well, she also has perfect timing.

37:06.467 --> 37:07.933
With the summer ending,

37:07.935 --> 37:10.319
it won't be as hard for Hankmed
to be Divya-less.

37:10.321 --> 37:12.354
I hope my opinion
will still be solicited.

37:12.356 --> 37:14.640
I can consult from the comfort
of my own bed,

37:14.642 --> 37:15.991
an iPad P.A.

37:15.993 --> 37:18.810
Hmm. Nice.

37:18.812 --> 37:20.145
Speaking of division of labor,

37:20.147 --> 37:21.864
I actually wanted to talk to you both.

37:21.866 --> 37:24.116
Divya, I'm not sure if
Jeremiah's told you about our...

37:24.118 --> 37:25.784
I'm up to speed.

37:25.786 --> 37:28.003
Okay.

37:28.005 --> 37:30.839
Jeremiah, I understand your hesitation

37:30.841 --> 37:32.658
to give Hankmed...

37:32.660 --> 37:37.046
well, to give me your trust again.

37:37.048 --> 37:39.715
But I have a proposal.

37:39.717 --> 37:41.967
What if you could return to Hankmed

37:41.969 --> 37:44.603
and not work with me at all?

37:44.605 --> 37:46.472
How would that be possible?

37:46.474 --> 37:50.726
You would be in charge, and I wouldn't.

38:02.789 --> 38:04.156
Russel's been discharged.

38:04.158 --> 38:06.909
That's great.

38:06.911 --> 38:11.747
He said to thank
his fearless scorpion hunter.

38:11.749 --> 38:14.300
Well, yeah.

38:14.302 --> 38:15.884
We make a pretty good team.

38:15.886 --> 38:19.171
We do.

38:19.173 --> 38:22.040
Why does it always take a crisis

38:22.042 --> 38:25.928
for this team to play well?

38:25.930 --> 38:27.563
Why does it take a historic blizzard

38:27.565 --> 38:30.399
or a fake auction sting

38:30.401 --> 38:32.818
or an actual scorpion sting

38:32.820 --> 38:35.887
for us to come together?

38:35.889 --> 38:37.773
You mean why do we have
a troubled romance?

38:37.775 --> 38:39.891
Yeah.

38:41.578 --> 38:42.778
Whew.

38:45.615 --> 38:47.916
With my campaign

38:47.918 --> 38:51.704
and your auction house,

38:51.706 --> 38:54.373
I kind of feel like our passion
this summer

38:54.375 --> 38:56.091
hasn't been for each other at all.

38:56.093 --> 38:58.210
It's been for our personal ambitions.

38:58.212 --> 39:00.679
It's not just this summer, Evan.

39:00.681 --> 39:01.880
Our marriage has been on hold

39:01.882 --> 39:05.250
since that crazy night it first began.

39:05.252 --> 39:06.719
Hank's surgery and then Hank's recovery

39:06.721 --> 39:09.421
and then my classes in the city.

39:09.423 --> 39:10.689
I don't wanna go to Paris

39:10.691 --> 39:12.358
if it's gonna keep us on hold.

39:12.360 --> 39:14.309
And I don't want you not to

39:14.311 --> 39:15.561
if it's gonna make you unhappy.

39:15.563 --> 39:20.315
II think we need distance

39:20.317 --> 39:21.817
from all the stuff
that's getting in the way

39:21.819 --> 39:23.935
of our marriage.

39:29.709 --> 39:33.796
There are four other council members.

39:33.798 --> 39:35.998
I'm sure they'll be able
to handle things

39:36.000 --> 39:38.384
for now, at least.

39:38.386 --> 39:41.553
What about the promises you made?

39:46.009 --> 39:49.061
I made some promises to you too.

39:54.601 --> 39:55.984
Kristof can go to Paris.

39:55.986 --> 39:59.354
Okay, then.

39:59.356 --> 40:02.808
We'll take the time we need
to work through this.

40:02.810 --> 40:04.810
First, we need to get married.

40:04.812 --> 40:05.911
Again.

40:05.913 --> 40:08.664
100%.

40:08.666 --> 40:10.165
And then, we need to focus on us.

40:10.167 --> 40:12.751
Exactly. We need to go

40:12.753 --> 40:15.421
- to marriage counseling.
- On our honeymoon.

40:17.173 --> 40:19.324
Marriage counseling.

40:19.326 --> 40:22.461
Honeymoon.

40:22.463 --> 40:24.963
Yeah.
[Laughs]

40:24.965 --> 40:27.499
Yeah.

40:27.501 --> 40:31.353
[Sighs]
[Sniffles]

40:31.355 --> 40:34.356
[Soft rock music]

40:34.358 --> 40:34.858
